title: Brianchon's theorem
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

In a hexagon which is circumscribed to a [[conic|Projective conic]], the three diagonals connecting opposite points intersect in one point.
This is the [[dual|Dual conic]] of [[Pascal's theorem]].